text.tspan: 1. Server state is unique by UUID. --> <UUID, server_state>
2. STATUS: server checks connection for all devices in registration, maintains a pool of alive clients.
Given <UUID, STATUS>, the client receives: timeout->server off; bind off or peer off/on.
3. When client's daemon service starts, send REG info to register on server (if not exists) with a random name, constant UNREG turns false;
else if failed (UNREG is true), upon the 1st STATUS or GETQN msg the server register it.
add device to alive client pool)
